<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Neat. I have another idea completely opposite.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Benign">Benign</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:28 p.m. 22/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Neat. I have another idea completely opposite.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2213" TARGET=_self>i have an idea - a chaos server</A> (Merzbow)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I like that chaos server idea, but the reason I don't like games like quake is because upon death you lose nothing. What is the point of fighting if you don't get stuff to show you are winning? I would like to see a server that swings the other direction. Permanent death and complete looting. No level limits to fighting and all that jazz. Immediately upon arrival into the world you would need to find a more powerful character willing to take you in(lest you be slayed by another). He would, knowing that the more people with him the higher his chance of survival. I am sure alot of people don't have the sack for it, but I would like to try it.

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
